{% import "macros/paths" as paths %}
Diff files (code actions, renames) are applied by deleting them (`rm`). Preview with the Read tool (normally not required), apply with `rm`.

```bash
# LSP rename — immediate, project-wide, always use this instead of manual renames across files
mv {{ paths.sym_dir("file." ~ ext, "old_name") }} {{ paths.sym_dir("file." ~ ext, "new_name") }}

# Apply symbol rename
rm {{ paths.sym_rename("file." ~ ext, "old_name", "new_name") }}

# List available LSP code actions:
ls {{ paths.sym_actions("file." ~ ext, "process") }}

# Preview a code action, then apply:
# Read {{ paths.sym_action("file." ~ ext, "process", "01-fix") }}
rm {{ paths.sym_action("file." ~ ext, "process", "01-fix") }}
```
